e, Black simply saves the b pawn. We can continue with our idea. } (6... Nf6 { Black accepts the fact that he'll lose b7, and continues development. } 7. Bc4! { The b7 pawn remains hanging. We can continue development first, adding pressure on f7. } 7... Qe7 (7... Qd7 8. Qxb7 $18) 8. Qxb7! { Nc3 is also playable, followed by Bg5 and castle. Going all out to attack. But this line keeps things simple, we end up with a winning endgame. } { [%csl Ra8] } 8... Qb4+ { Black must trade queens in order not to lose material. } 9. Qxb4 Bxb4+ 10. c3 { [%cal Rc3b4] } 10... Bc5 11. f3 $16 { Solidifying. This is just better for White with the extra pawn and 2 pawn islands compared to Black's 3. } { [%csl Gf3,Ge4,Gg2,Ra7,Rc7][%cal Bb1d2,Bc4b3,Bd2c4,Bc1g5] }) (6... Qc8? 7. Bc4 $18 { Black's completely lost. The f7-pawn will fall. If Nh6, we simply get rid of it with Bxh6. And if the queen defends f7, b7 is left hanging. } { [%csl Rf7,Rb7] }) (6... Nd7 7. Qxb7 Rb8 8. Qxa7 Bc5 9. Qa6! $16 { The key move. Other moves may allows Black to get counterplay. Next retreat to e2 and White's better with the 2 extra pawns. } { [%csl Be2][%cal Ba6e2] }) 7. Bc4! { [%csl Rf7][%cal Gb3f7] } 7... Qe7 { Black protects the important f7 pawn. White has a really nice counter move here: } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Ge7f7] } (7... Qd7 8. Nc3 { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bc3d5] } 8... Nf6 (8... a6 { Top engine, stopping Nb5. } 9. Nd5 { White has the bishop pair and nice development. Next up is Qg3, rerouting the queen to a better place. And castle queenside. } { [%csl Gd5,Bg3][%cal Bb3g3,Bc1e3,Be1c1] }) 9. Bg5 $18 { There really isn't anything for black to do now: Be7 hangs the f pawn, c6 results to 10. Rd8! and on the next move we take the knight and black's structure is total trash, and Nc6 results to Bb5! and black is completely miserable. }) (7... Qf6 8. Nc3! { [%cal Bc3d5,Bc3b5] } 8... c6 9. Nd5! cxd5 10. Bb5+!! Nd7 (10... Nc6 11. Bg5!! Qg6 12. Qxd5 { [%csl Rc6] } 12... Rc8 13. O-O-O { [%csl Gd8][%cal Gd2d8] } 13... Qxg5+ 14. f4!! Qxf4+ 15. Kb1 { [%csl Gd7,Gc6] } 15... Bc5 16. Qd7+ Kf8 17. Qxc8+ Ke7 18. Qxc6 $18 { [%csl Re7,Gd8,Gd7,Bf6,Be6,Bd6,Be8][%cal Gd1d8,Bc6f6,Bc6e8] }) 11. Bxd7+ Kxd7 12. Qxd5+ $18 { [%csl Ga8,Gd7][%cal Gd5a8,Gd5d7] }) 8. Bg5! { Sacrificing the bishop! A deflection! If the queen takes the bishop, f7 is left hanging. White wins material after a rather long sequence. (see variation) } 8... f6 (8... Qxg5 9. Bxf7+! Kd8 (9... Ke7 10. Qe6+ Kd8 11. Qe8# { GG } { [%csl Gc8,Gd8,Gd7,Rc7,Ge7,Be8][%cal Ge8c8,Ge8d7,Ge8e7,Bf7e8] }) (9... Kd7 10. Qe6+ Kd8 11. Qe8#) 10. Qd5+ { Forking } { [%csl Gd8,Ga8][%cal Gd5a8,Gd5d8] } 10... Bd6 11. Qxa8 Qc1+ { Black might think that they're okay, because black will win our rook, but now the knight is undefended. } 12. Ke2 Qxh1 (12... Qxc2+ { A attempt to get a 3 fold repetition. } 13. Nd2 $18 { The only move that wins. Black has no checks anymore. White wins a large amount of material. } { [%csl Rb8] }) 13. Qxb8+ Ke7 14. Qe8+ Kf6 15. Qe6+ Kg5 16. Qf5+ Kh4 17. Qh5# { [%csl Yh3,Yg3,Gh4,Gg4,Bh5,Gg5][%cal Yg2h3,Yh2g3,Gh5h4,Gh5g4,Bf7h5,Gh5g5] }) (8... Nf6 9. Nc3! { Getting ready to castle and we want to hop the horse into d5. } { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bc3d5] } 9... Nbd7 10. Nd5 Qd6 11. O-O-O Nxd5 12. Bxd5 $18 { There are too many threats for Black to deal with. If Black saves the rook, White wins the queen with Bxf7!, if Black saves the queen, White happily takes the rook on a8. } { [%csl Ra8,Rf7] }) 9. Bd2 { The knight on g8 is hanging and we prepare for a potential Bb4 in the future. } { [%csl Gb4,Rg8][%cal Gd2b4] } 9... Nh6 { The only move that saves the knight. } 10. Bxh6 gxh6 { [%csl Rh7,Rh6] } 11. Nc3! { Even though material is equal currently, Black is completely lost. His king is much too weak and has no well placed pieces. Moves like Nd5, castling queenside or Bd5 are coming. } { [%csl Bd5,Bc1,Rf8,Rb8,Ra8,Re7,Rf6,Re5,Rc7,Rb6,Gb3,Gc4][%cal Bc3d5,Be1c1] } 11... c6 { Black prevents Nd5, or does he? } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rc6d5] } 12. Nd5! { Hopping in anyway! } 12... cxd5 13. Bxd5 $18 { It's over. } { [%csl Ra8,Re8,Re7][%cal Gd5a8,Be1c1] } *


